Alembic - Migrations

FREQUENT COMMANDS
-----------------

Generate a new migration (review before applying):
  docker compose exec api alembic revision --autogenerate -m "short_description"

Apply all pending migrations:
  docker compose exec api alembic upgrade head

View current DB state:
  docker compose exec api alembic current

View history:
  docker compose exec api alembic history --verbose

Revert a migration:
  docker compose exec api alembic downgrade -1

Reset DB (dev only, deletes data):
  docker compose down -v
  docker compose up -d

RULES
-----

- Never edit an already applied migration. Create a new one with autogenerate.
- Always review the generated file before applying it.
- Migrations run in CI before tests.
- The FK to projects.id in user_roles.project_id is added when the Project model is created.